  "polemic_chains_field_doc": "Each thinker JSON may carry an optional 'polemic_chain_ids' string-array listing chain_ids in which the thinker is engaged as attacker, target, or responder. The canonical chain definitions live in data/polemic_chains/<chain-id>.json; these are argument-by-argument reconstructions (premise → inference → conclusion) of major Vedāntic refutations, with explicit 'what_it_touches' analysis of which earlier positions the polemic actually engages versus leaves intact. The field is parallel to comparative_claim_ids but tracks a different unit (a multi-argument polemic chain rather than a single pairwise claim).",
